snippet: The New Jersey Symphony Orchestra, led by Jacques Lacombe, ended its season with performances of Mahler’s Ninth Symphony, a bold undertaking for a smallish ensemble.
abstract: James R Oestreich reviews concert of Mahler works, performed by the New Jersey Symphony Orchestra and led by Jacques Lacombe, at the New Jersey Performing Arts Center.
lead_paragraph: The New Jersey Symphony Orchestra, led by Jacques Lacombe, ended its season with performances of Mahler’s Ninth Symphony, a bold undertaking for a smallish ensemble.

headline.seo: Jacques Lacombe and the New Jersey Symphony Orchestra
headline.main: A Mahler That Stands or Falls on Its Finale
headline.print_headline: A Mahler Work That Stands or Falls on Its Finale
